==English==

===Etymology===
From {{etyl|la|en}} {{term|minimus||lang=la|least, smallest}}

===Pronunciation===
* {{audio|En-us-minimum.ogg|Audio (US)|lang=en}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun|s|minima}}

# The [[lowest]] [[limit]].
#: ''We prefer candidates with a '''minimum''' of 4 years experience in the field.''
#: ''We need a '''minimum''' of 3 fully-qualified staff members on duty at all time.''
# The [[smallest]] [[amount]].
#: ''He always tries to get away with doing the '''minimum'''.''
#: ''Please keep noise to a '''minimum''' after 11 o'clock''
# {{context|astronomy|lang=en}} A period of minimum [[brightness]] or [[energy]] [[intensity]] (of a [[star]]).
#: {{usex|The Maunder '''minimum''' of the Sun reportedly corresponded to a period of great cold on Earth.|lang=en}}
# {{context|analysis|lang=en}} A [[lower bound]] of a set which is also an element of that set.
# {{context|statistics|lang=en}} The smallest member of a [[batch]] or [[sample]] or the lower bound of a [[probability distribution]].

====Usage notes====
* {{term|minima|Minima}} is more common plural for the technical senses.

